\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*}[{\rm{RNA}}\;{\rm{ribonucleotide}}(\mu {\rm{M}})] = ({\rm{R}}/({\rm{R}} + {\rm{A}})*([{\rm{ATP}}])(\mu {\rm{M}})\end{equation*}\end{document}where R refers to the band intensity observed for each ribonucleotide, A is the intensity of the radioactively label ATP substrate and [ATP] refers to the total molar concentration of ATP (labeled and unlabeled). The molar amount of RNA products is obtained by dividing the number of ATPs in the RNA chain.
